s. Many governmental powers have been shifted toward a host of network parties such as NGOs, state enterprises, international organizations, autonomous agencies, and local governments. Governments have developed complex networks for service delivery and they have a strategic interest in the news media as an arena where their interests can be served and threatened. How do the media relate to and report on complex systems of government? How do the various governance actors respond to the media and what are the effects on their policies? This book considers the impact of media-related factors on governance, policy, public accountability and the attribution of blame for failures.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mai 2023) 7aPOLITICAL SCIENCE / General.2bisacsh1 aAlon-Barkat, Saar, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aChristmann, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDjerf-Pierre, Monika, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFriedrichsmeier, Andres, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilad, Sharon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHasler, Karin, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJacobs, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlijn, Erik Hans, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKübler, Daniel, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarcinkowksi, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMarcinkowski, Frank, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPeters, B. Guy, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPierre, Jon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/v